Name: Configuration Control
Text:
Configuration control defines:

  * the documentation of the actual configuration, 
  * the procedures for configuration change,
  * the procedures for preventing unauthorized items from entering service, 
  * the access to configuration tools,
  * the traceability of HW and SW- versions, 
  * the traceability of configuration changes
    (e.g. identification of last revision).

IncludeRequirements: full

